# API Design Rules

## URL Conventions

### ✅ Use kebab-case for URLs:
```python
# Correct
router = APIRouter(prefix="/test-cases", tags=["Test Cases"])

@router.get("/feature/{feature_id}/test-cases")
@router.post("/bulk-status")
```

### ❌ NEVER use:
```python
# Wrong: snake_case
@router.get("/test_cases")

# Wrong: camelCase
@router.get("/testCases")
```

---

## HTTP Methods

| Action | Method | URL Pattern | Example |
|--------|--------|-------------|---------|
| List | GET | `/resources` | `GET /features` |
| Get one | GET | `/resources/{id}` | `GET /features/1` |
| Create | POST | `/resources` | `POST /features` |
| Full update | PUT | `/resources/{id}` | `PUT /features/1` |
| Partial update | PATCH | `/resources/{id}` | `PATCH /features/1` |
| Delete | DELETE | `/resources/{id}` | `DELETE /features/1` |
| Action | POST | `/resources/{id}/action` | `POST /test-cases/1/accept` |

---

## Response Codes

```python
from fastapi import status

# 200 OK - Successful GET, PATCH
@router.get("/", response_model=list[FeatureRead])
def list_features(): ...

# 201 Created - Successful POST
@router.post("/", response_model=FeatureRead, status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED)
def create_feature(): ...

# 204 No Content - Successful DELETE
@router.delete("/{id}", status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)
def delete_feature(): ...

# 400 Bad Request - Invalid input
raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Invalid data")

# 401 Unauthorized - Missing/invalid auth
raise HTTPException(status_code=401, detail="Authentication required")

# 403 Forbidden - Authenticated but not allowed
raise HTTPException(status_code=403, detail="Not authorized")

# 404 Not Found - Resource doesn't exist
raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="Feature not found")

# 422 Unprocessable Entity - Validation failed (automatic from Pydantic)

# 429 Too Many Requests - Rate limited
raise HTTPException(status_code=429, detail="Rate limit exceeded")

# 500 Internal Server Error - Unexpected error (should be rare)
```

